sentences: Barry Young (né Clarence LaVonne Fitzgerald; June 27, 1931 in Oklahoma – December 2, 1966 in Los Angeles) was an American pop singer who recorded for Dot Records in the 1960s.
His biggest hit single was a recording of the tune "One Has My Name (The Other Has My Heart)," which had previously been a number 1 hit on the country charts for Jimmy Wakely in 1948.
